summary:
**Summary of ASX Announcement (Dateline Resources Limited - DTR):**  

- **Exploration Update (Colosseum Gold-REE Project, California):**  
  - **Geophysical Survey Progress:** Magnetotelluric (MT) survey 70% complete (119/167 stations). Initial 2D resistivity data under review.  
  - **Timing:** Survey to finish in ~2 weeks; 3D inversion results expected 2–4 weeks post-completion.  
  - **Geochemical Sampling:** 599 of 1,200 samples collected (~50% complete). Remainder expected in 17–20 days. Initial assay results anticipated in July.  

- **Resource Context (Previously Disclosed):**  
  - JORC Resource: 27.1Mt @ 1.26g/t Au (1.1Moz Au), with 67% in Measured & Indicated categories.  
  - REE potential highlighted due to proximity to Mountain Pass mine.  

**No material capital markets or liquidity-impacting updates identified.**  

*(Note: Announcement primarily covers exploration progress; no new financial, capital raising, or material operational changes disclosed.)*
